The paper deals with the formation of teams in multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the stability and approximation of the team formation process, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of a bipartite network and the analysis of convergence to a stable solution indicate that the paper could also be classified under Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the proposed algorithm for team formation involves local rules and the analysis of performance, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
